<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1903-01-05T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1903-01-05T00:00:00-05:00" n="328" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d328">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Hay</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Swenson</persName></hi>.</head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1903-01-05"><hi rend="italic">January 5,
                                1903</hi></date>.</dateline>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 163.]</seg></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have to acknowledge the receipt of your
                            No. 286, of the 16th ultimo, inclosing copies of correspondence with Mr.
                            C. Ravn respecting the status of his citizenship.</p>
                        <p>Your views on the subject, as expressed in your letter of February 17,
                            1902, to that gentleman, are commended by the Department.</p>
                        <p>I am, etc.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">John Hay</hi>.</signed></closer>
                    </div>
                </body></text></TEI>